Q: How to prevent an iframe from reloading when moving it in the DOM A: <p>Use <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/moveBefore" rel="nofollow noreferrer">the <code>moveBefore</code> API</a> to move while keeping the state:</p>
<p>Warning: Safari <a href="https://caniuse.com/?search=moveBefore" rel="nofollow noreferrer">does not currently implement it</a> :(</p>
<p>you can do something like this for the implementation:</p>
<pre><code>  if ('moveBefore' in targetContainer) {
    // (targetContainer as any).moveBefore(element, null) // Typescript support is limited
    targetContainer.moveBefore(element, null)
  } else {
    // Fallback: appendChild also moves without cloning
    targetContainer.appendChild(element)
  }
</code></pre>
<p>In case you use a web component, you would need to implement <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_components/Using_custom_elements#lifecycle_callbacks_and_state-preserving_moves" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>connectedMoveCallback</code></a></p>

Q: TouchBehavior doesn&#39;t work correctly on custom control A: <p>If it acts and feels like a Button, then, it is a Button. The reason why is it is pretty hard to replicate all the things a Button does, so, you should just use a Button. (e.g. press, accessibility - semantic description, keyboard shortcuts).</p>
<pre class="lang-xml prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;ContentView&gt;
    &lt;Grid&gt;
        &lt;!-- Start your visual representation --&gt;
        &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
        &lt;!-- End your visual representation --&gt;

        &lt;!-- Start of invisible Button --&gt;
        &lt;Button BackgroundColor=&quot;Transparent&quot; Text=&quot;Invisible Button&quot; TextColor=&quot;Transparent&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;!-- End of invisible button --&gt;
    &lt;/Grid&gt;
&lt;/ContentView&gt;
</code></pre>

Q: I need to access the &quot;canSeePlayer&quot; property in the playerController script from enemies script A: <p>Since you anyway use the triggers be aware: Trigger events are called on both parties of the collision, the enemy and the player itself</p>
<p>I would rather simply shift the logic to the player directly and do e.g. something like</p>
<p>(in the <code>PlayerCobtroller</code>)</p>
<pre><code>private void OnTriggerStay2D(Collider2D collision)
{
    if (collision.CompareTag(&quot;Enemy&quot;))
    {
        // Note btw: way easier to use a Linecast instead of a Raycast here
        var canSeePlayer = !Physics2D.LineCast(transform.position, collision.transform.position, obstructionLayer);

        if(canSeePlayer)
        {
          // =&gt; GAME OVER HERE
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Now since <code>OnTrigger2DStay</code> is anyway called once for each and every enemy within your trigger range there is no need keep track of enemy instances in a list etc at all.</p>
